00:00:08.940 --> 00:00:10.280
BUILD IT

00:00:10.280 --> 00:00:15.120
Lionel Buckett is building a Luxury retreat
into a cliff top cave.

00:00:15.120 --> 00:00:20.269
Located near Sydney Australia the finished
work will feature a running waterfall, spa,

00:00:20.269 --> 00:00:21.590
and even a bar.

00:00:21.590 --> 00:00:25.929
The cave will be finished in a few months
and it will offer tours of the local rainforest

00:00:25.929 --> 00:00:30.240
as well as provide an excellent site for photo
shoots and film making.

00:00:30.240 --> 00:00:32.580
Michael Warren made a glowing table.

00:00:32.580 --> 00:00:37.520
By mixing photoluminescent powder into clear
resin and then pouring it over damaged wood

00:00:37.520 --> 00:00:40.470
he creates the appearance of a bioluminescent
table.

00:00:40.470 --> 00:00:44.930
And he setup a page on Instructables explaining
exactly how he made it.

00:00:44.930 --> 00:00:50.790
Former special effects artist Kazuhiro Tsuji
creates life-like portraits of famous people.

00:00:50.790 --> 00:00:55.610
The busts are built to two times life size,
and are constructed with a variety of materials

00:00:55.610 --> 00:00:57.730
including resin and silicon.

00:00:57.730 --> 00:01:01.420
Each piece takes him up to four months to
make, and he says he likes to create them

00:01:01.420 --> 00:01:05.939
with a neutral expression so that viewers
are left wondering what each figure might

00:01:05.939 --> 00:01:07.530
be thinking.

00:01:07.530 --> 00:01:08.530
DRAW IT

00:01:08.530 --> 00:01:11.829
Nathan Shields creates portraits with pancakes.

00:01:11.829 --> 00:01:17.869
The Math teacher from Washington uses 12oz
wide-mouth squeeze bottles to make his Saipaincakes.

00:01:17.869 --> 00:01:20.200
Which originated during a trip with his kids
to Saipan.

00:01:20.200 --> 00:01:25.140
And he’s used batter for portraits ranging
from Martin Luther King and Leonardo Da Vinci

00:01:25.140 --> 00:01:27.640
to Angry Birds and The Hobbit.

00:01:27.640 --> 00:01:32.549
Davit Yukhanyan creates surrealist images
that house hundreds of smaller drawings.

00:01:32.549 --> 00:01:37.469
He’s an architect in Armenia that draws
in his spare time and the smaller illustrations

00:01:37.469 --> 00:01:40.299
contribute to the narrative of the main picture.

00:01:40.299 --> 00:01:44.689
And they explore themes of the subconscious,
dreams and lobster.

00:01:44.689 --> 00:01:58.780
And for now the hand-painting illusions of
Luca Luce…

00:01:58.780 --> 00:02:04.970
Sergio Odeith makes murals that appear burst
off the walls in 3-D. The Portuguese artist

00:02:04.970 --> 00:02:09.740
has been spray-painting street art for decades
and his anamorphic style creates an optical

00:02:09.740 --> 00:02:11.590
illusion on 90 degree corners.

00:02:11.590 --> 00:02:17.450
But if you’re not in Lisbon to see his work
in person you can find prints on his website.

00:02:17.450 --> 00:02:18.450
